+## Period Format Rules
+
+Different command groups use different time formats. Do not assume every command accepts `YYYY-MM-DD`.
+
+### `certificate list`
+
+`certificate list --start/--end` uses **accounting periods** in `YYYYMM` format.
+
+Correct:
+
+```bash
+# January 2021 only
+cli-anything-wukong certificate list --start 202101 --end 202101
+
+# Full year 2024
+cli-anything-wukong certificate list --start 202401 --end 202412
+```
+
+Incorrect:
+
+```bash
+# This command may return misleading empty results
+cli-anything-wukong certificate list --start 2021-01-01 --end 2021-01-31
+```
+
+Reason: the backend filters voucher periods using `DATE_FORMAT(certificate_time, '%Y%m')`, so this command is period-based, not natural-date-based.
+
+### `report` commands
+
+`report balance-sheet`, `report income`, and `report cash-flow` use a **period end date** in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
+
+```bash
+cli-anything-wukong report balance-sheet --period month --date 2021-01-31
+cli-anything-wukong report income --period month --date 2021-01-31
+cli-anything-wukong report cash-flow --period month --date 2021-01-31
+```
+
+### `ledger` commands
+
+`ledger detail`, `ledger general`, and `ledger balance` use natural dates in `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
+
+```bash
+cli-anything-wukong ledger balance --start 2021-01-01 --end 2021-01-31
+```
+
